12:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Aider and Codium AI share a solid foundation of core features including Debugging, Test Generation, Multi Language. Where Aider pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Code Generation and Refactoring and Chat, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Codium AI uniquely offers Code Review and Ide Integration, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Aider holds an overall score of 8/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while Codium AI scores 7/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
13:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Aider offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $0, compared to Codium AI's starting price of $19/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Aider's free tier and Codium AI's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
